{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "vp-backend-by-abuzar-2026-05-20",
    "name": "VidyaPrayag API (backend-by-abuzar)",
    "description": "End-to-end Postman collection for the Ktor backend introduced in PR #1 (branch `backend-by-abuzar`).\n\nCovers all 23 endpoints across 9 feature groups: landing, app-status, auth (+ legacy aliases), user details, user profile, onboarding, announcements, admissions, school (analytics / calendar / holidays / attendance).\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Import this collection AND `VidyaPrayag.local.postman_environment.json` into Postman.\n2. Select the **VidyaPrayag — Local** environment in the top-right dropdown.\n3. Make sure `{{baseUrl}}` points to your running server (default `http://localhost:8080`).\n4. Run the requests **in order from the first folder to the last**. The login/signup requests have test scripts that auto-store `token`, `refreshToken` and `userId` into the environment — every subsequent authenticated request reads `{{token}}` automatically.\n\nSee `docs/backend/POSTMAN_TESTING_GUIDE.md` for the full step-by-step walkthrough.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// No-op global pre-request. Per-request scripts handle token saving."
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Liveness",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET / (root greeting)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": [""] },
            "description": "Liveness check. Should return a plain-text greeting like:\n`Ktor: Hello, Java! — VidyaPrayag API v1 is live`"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1. Landing (public)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/content/landing",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/content/landing", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "content", "landing"] },
            "description": "Returns CMS-driven landing-page content (taglines, login modes, parent/school info blocks, offerings, portals). Seeded by `Seed.kt → seedLanding()`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. App Status (public)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/config/app-status",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "App-Version", "value": "2.4.0" },
              { "key": "Platform", "value": "android" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/config/app-status", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "config", "app-status"] },
            "description": "Returns version-check + maintenance + feature flags. Used by the Splash screen."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Auth (public)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/check-user (existing demo admin)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"demo.admin@vidyaprayag.com\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/check-user", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "check-user"] },
            "description": "The seeded demo admin already exists, so this should return `is_new_user: false`.\n\nThe alias `/auth/check-user` (without `/api/v1`) also works for legacy clients."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/check-user (brand-new contact)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"[email protected]\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/check-user", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "check-user"] },
            "description": "Should return `is_new_user: true` and `auth_method_required: \"PASSWORD\"` because the identifier looks like an email."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/signup (email + password — ADMIN)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Signup returns 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Envelope success=true', () => pm.expect(json.success).to.eql(true));",
                  "pm.test('Returns token', () => pm.expect(json.data.token).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "// Persist token + ids for later authenticated requests.",
                  "pm.environment.set('token', json.data.token);",
                  "pm.environment.set('refreshToken', json.data.refresh_token);",
                  "pm.environment.set('userId', json.data.user_id);",
                  "pm.environment.set('role', json.data.role);",
                  "console.log('Saved token for user', json.data.user_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Postman Tester\",\n  \"identifier\": \"[email protected]\",\n  \"password\": \"hunter2\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\",\n  \"device_info\": {\n    \"device_id\": \"postman-1\",\n    \"platform\": \"web\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/signup", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "signup"] },
            "description": "Creates a brand-new ADMIN account and **automatically saves the JWT into `{{token}}`** for the rest of this collection.\n\nRe-running this exact request will return 409 (account exists). Change the email to test again, or just run the login below."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/login (email + password — re-login)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Login returns 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.environment.set('token', json.data.token);",
                  "pm.environment.set('refreshToken', json.data.refresh_token);",
                  "pm.environment.set('userId', json.data.user_id);",
                  "pm.environment.set('role', json.data.role);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"[email protected]\",\n  \"password\": \"hunter2\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] },
            "description": "Re-issues a JWT for the account created above. Use this if you closed Postman and lost `{{token}}`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/send-otp (mock)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"9876543210\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/send-otp", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "send-otp"] },
            "description": "Always returns success and the dev OTP is **`123456`** (see `AuthRouting.kt` — this is a mock until an SMS provider is wired in)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/signup (phone + OTP — ADMIN, optional)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.environment.set('token', json.data.token);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('userId', json.data.user_id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Phone Tester\",\n  \"identifier\": \"9000000001\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/signup", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "signup"] },
            "description": "Optional: shows the phone+OTP signup path. The hard-coded dev OTP is `123456`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. User Details (jwt)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/user/details",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/user/details", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "user", "details"] },
            "description": "Returns the logged-in user's identity + onboarding step status (BASIC / BRANDING / ACADEMIC / REVIEW with COMPLETED/PENDING/LOCKED).\n\nUses `{{token}}` automatically."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Onboarding (jwt)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=BASIC",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=BASIC",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "step"],
              "query": [{ "key": "obStepType", "value": "BASIC" }]
            },
            "description": "Returns the dynamic field list for the BASIC step (school_name, board_affiliation, official_email, contact_number, country_code, address)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/v1/onboarding/submit (BASIC)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"ob_step_type\": \"BASIC\",\n  \"is_final_submission\": false,\n  \"data_payload\": {\n    \"school_name\": \"Postman Test Academy\",\n    \"board_affiliation\": \"CBSE\",\n    \"official_email\": \"[email protected]\",\n    \"contact_number\": \"9000000001\",\n    \"country_code\": \"+91\",\n    \"address\": \"Test Lane, Sector 1, New Delhi\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/submit", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "submit"] },
            "description": "Saves BASIC step drafts. `next_step` should be `\"BRANDING\"`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=BRANDING",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=BRANDING",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "step"],
              "query": [{ "key": "obStepType", "value": "BRANDING" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/v1/onboarding/submit (BRANDING)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"ob_step_type\": \"BRANDING\",\n  \"is_final_submission\": false,\n  \"data_payload\": {\n    \"logo_url\": \"https://example.com/logo.png\",\n    \"theme_color\": \"#0F62FE\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/submit", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "submit"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=ACADEMIC",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=ACADEMIC",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "step"],
              "query": [{ "key": "obStepType", "value": "ACADEMIC" }]
            },
            "description": "Returns `list_of_active_classes` for the user's school (empty for brand-new accounts; the demo admin has Grade 10 + Grade 5)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/onboarding/academic/class-details?classId=C10",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/academic/class-details?classId=C10",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "academic", "class-details"],
              "query": [{ "key": "classId", "value": "C10" }]
            },
            "description": "Lists the subjects under classId=`C10` (Grade 10) for the demo school. Returns 404 if the new account has no class C10 yet — log in as the demo admin to see seeded data (see guide)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=REVIEW",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/step?obStepType=REVIEW",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "step"],
              "query": [{ "key": "obStepType", "value": "REVIEW" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/v1/onboarding/submit (REVIEW — final)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"ob_step_type\": \"REVIEW\",\n  \"is_final_submission\": true,\n  \"data_payload\": {}\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/submit", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "onboarding", "submit"] },
            "description": "Final submission. Promotes drafts → SchoolTable, flips `onboarding_status` to `COMPLETED`. Response: `is_onboarding_complete=true`, `redirect_to_home=true`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Announcements (jwt)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/school/announcements",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/school/announcements", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "school", "announcements"] },
            "description": "All announcements for the user's school, newest first."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/v1/school/announcements/search?query=summer",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/school/announcements/search?query=summer",
